<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-19158] camel-core: ThrowExceptionProcessor may silently ignore exceptions in constructing the exception object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-19158</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Back in Camel 3.12, a change was made to ThrowExceptionProcessor: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/fb0528706d7e8a7d0d6ba22dfb649cb31cf06bc8/core/camel-core-processor/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/processor/ThrowExceptionProcessor.java#L77-L82&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/fb0528706d7e8a7d0d6ba22dfb649cb31cf06bc8/core/camel-core-processor/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/processor/ThrowExceptionProcessor.java#L77-L82&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you happen to drop into the else clause, then no exception is set on the exchange and it&apos;s confusing to users as to why no exception was thrown in their route. This is potentially a common thing on Camel Quarkus native mode if the specific exception type was not registered for reflection.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
